{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "/nodes/sop/MOPS--Mesh_Flow-1.1/mops_modifier_02.svg", "type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "Mesh_Flow", "version": "1.1", "namespace": "MOPS"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["MOPs Orient Mesh"], "extent": [0, 21]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": [" Initializes N and up vectors for use by MOPs Move Along Mesh. "], "extent": [58, 129]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The MOPs Orient Mesh Modifier can be used to quickly generate normal and up vectors for use by MOPs Move Along Mesh. The resulting vectors can be further modified by a Comb SOP or any other point operation."], "extent": [129, 337]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [337, 352], "body": []}, {"level": 1, "id": "inputs", "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [352, 361], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Input Mesh"], "extent": [361, 373], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The polygon mesh to generate flow vectors on."], "extent": [373, 428]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "text": "Inputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [428, 440], "body": [{"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["General"], "extent": [440, 455], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Compute Method"], "extent": [455, 472], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The method by which to compute the flow vectors on the mesh."], "extent": [496, 561]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Compute From Polygons: Use the mesh topology to automatically create normal and up vectors. This behavior is identical to using the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/polyframe", "type": "link", "text": ["Polyframe SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/polyframe"}, "."], "extent": [561, 735]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["N and Up: Use existing mesh normals plus a defined up vector."], "extent": [735, 803]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use Orient: Use an existing p@orient quaternion attribute."], "extent": [803, 873]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "compute_method"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Compute Normals"], "extent": [873, 890], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Compute point normals on the input mesh."], "extent": [909, 959]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "do_normal"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Create Up"], "extent": [959, 970], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Create a v@up point attribute on the input mesh."], "extent": [985, 1039]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "do_up"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Auto Up"], "extent": [1039, 1048], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If enabled, automatically compute the up vector by calculating the difference between the local N and world N (+Z), then applying that same difference to world up (+Y). This matches the behavior of the Copy SOP when an ", {"type": "code", "text": ["up"]}, " attribute is undefined."], "extent": [1065, 1322]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "auto_up"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Up Vector"], "extent": [1322, 1333], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The up vector to use with the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["N and Up"]}, " Compute Method if ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Create Up"]}, " is enabled."], "extent": [1352, 1449]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "up_vector"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Invert N"], "extent": [1449, 1459], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Invert the existing point normals."], "extent": [1477, 1521]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "invert_N"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Invert Up"], "extent": [1521, 1532], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Invert the up vector."], "extent": [1551, 1582]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "invert_up"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Cross Up Vector"], "extent": [1582, 1599], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Compute the cross product of the existing up vector with the normal vector, and bind the result to up. This can create the effect of the up vectors ", {"type": "q", "text": ["flowing"]}, " over the surface."], "extent": [1617, 1802]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "do_cross"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Enable Curl Noise"], "extent": [1802, 1821], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Blend the mesh flow vectors with curl noise."], "extent": [1838, 1892]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "do_curl"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Enable Blur"], "extent": [1892, 1905], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Blur the resulting N and up vectors after computing them."], "extent": [1922, 1988]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "do_blur"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Curl Noise"], "extent": [1988, 2005], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Blend With Original"], "extent": [2005, 2027], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The amount to blend the curl noise in with the initial flow vectors. A value of 1.0 outputs entirely curl noise."], "extent": [2041, 2163]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "bias"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Use Rest Position"], "extent": [2163, 2182], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If the input mesh has a v@rest point attribute, use this attribute to lookup the noise values instead of position (@P)."], "extent": [2200, 2329]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "use_rest"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Blur"], "extent": [2329, 2340], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["See the Attribute Blur SOP for details."], "extent": [2340, 2380]}]}], "text": "Parameters"}], "title": ["MOPs Orient Mesh"], "summary": [" Initializes N and up vectors for use by MOPs Move Along Mesh. "]}